57.4	E-mail_address_harvesting	Email address harvesting	Furthermore, website operators may not distribute their legitimately collected lists. The CAN-SPAM Act of 2003 requires operators of web sites and online services should include a notice that the site or service will not give, sell, or otherwise transfer addresses maintained by such website or online service to any other party for the purposes of initiating, or enabling others to initiate, electronic mail messages.	
